    </p> <h4 data-v-60ddaa04=3D"" class=3D"steps h6">
      Steps for Calculating the Mean
    </h4> <p data-v-60ddaa04=3D"" class=3D"bottom-margins">
      There are three steps for calculating the mean:
    </p> <ol data-v-60ddaa04=3D"" class=3D"bottom-margins-mean"><li data-v-=
60ddaa04=3D"">Add up all the values in the dataset.</li> <li data-v-60ddaa0=
4=3D"">Count the number of observations.</li> <li data-v-60ddaa04=3D"">Divi=
de the sum by the number of observations.</li></ol> <p data-v-60ddaa04=3D""=
 class=3D"paragraph-mean">
      The result is the mean of the dataset.
    </p> <h4 data-v-60ddaa04=3D"" class=3D"h6">
      Advantages and Disadvantages of the Mean
    </h4> <p data-v-60ddaa04=3D"" class=3D"paragraph-one-advantages">
      The main advantage of the arithmetic mean is that it is <span data-v-=
60ddaa04=3D"" class=3D"bolded-texts">simple to understand</span> and <span =
data-v-60ddaa04=3D"" class=3D"bolded-texts">easy to calculate</span>. Moreo=
ver=E2=80=94compared to the other two measures of central tendency (median =
and mode)=E2=80=94the mean <span data-v-60ddaa04=3D"" class=3D"bolded-texts=
">considers all available information</span> about the size and magnitude o=
f the observations.
